# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# DNS Configuration:
#   Pi-hole local DNS entries point *.cronova.dev → 192.168.0.10 (Docker VM).
#   Required entries: vault, jara, yrasema, taguato, japysaka, taanga, aoao,
#                     git, auth, ysyry, kuatia, mbyja, aranduka, papa, vera
#
# Authelia-protected services:
#   japysaka (Sonarr), taanga (Radarr), aoao (Prowlarr),
#   ysyry (Dozzle), kuatia (BentoPDF), mbyja (Homepage), aranduka (Paperless),
#   papa (Grafana)
#
# Services with their own auth (NOT protected by Authelia):
#   jara (Home Assistant), taguato (Frigate), vault (Vaultwarden),
#   vera (Immich), git (Forgejo), yrasema (Jellyfin)
#
# Direct Access (no reverse proxy needed):
#   - Pi-hole: http://192.168.0.10:80/admin
#   - Home Assistant: http://192.168.0.10:8123
#   - Jellyfin: http://192.168.0.10:8096
#   - Frigate: https://taguato.cronova.dev (port 5000 localhost-only)
#
# Intentionally NOT proxied:
#   - qBittorrent (127.0.0.1:8081): History of CVEs (path traversal, RCE via
#     default creds, crypto mining exploits). Access via SSH tunnel or Tailscale:
#     ssh -L 8081:localhost:8081 docker-vm
#
# Docker Network:
#   Caddy uses caddy-net to reach services bound to 127.0.0.1 (by container name).
#   Services on 0.0.0.0 (HA, Vaultwarden, Jellyfin, *arr) use host.docker.internal.
#   Requires: extra_hosts: ["host.docker.internal:host-gateway"]
#
# =============================================================================
